travis: replace Fedora rawhide with Fedora 33

There have been CI failures with Fedora rawhide Docker images and it
turns out that upstream Docker image repository is not building ppc64le
Fedora rawhide and Fedora 34 Docker images. For details see:
https://github.com/docker-library/official-images/commit/f7c0d815ff9885b28e3b5a522b2c9bc9029943c9

For now, let keep travis happy with switch over to Fedora 33.

Output alignment issues in sl_printf

Commit c7dd78a fixed the output alignment issue in "v29_print.c". The same commit is getting
backported to the servicelog.c and also taking care the issues mentioned below.

If there were two consecutive newline characters, the snprintf would be called with length
set to 1. The snprintf returns the destination string length instead of the actual length written
over the buffer, which breaks the logic. To get rid of such issues, the fixes introduced to write
the newline explicitly and adjust the buf_offset.

Fix segfault on servicelog_open() failure

test_libservicelog.c tries to call servicelog_error() on failure from
servicelog_open().  But servicelog_open() only returns a non-NULL object
on success, so this is always wrong and results in a segfault.  Call
strerror() on the return code instead.

Signed-off-by: Steve Langasek <steve.langasek@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Ankit Kumar <ankit@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: Vasant Hegde <hegdevasant@linux.vnet.ibm.com>

Use libtool dependencies for linking tests

If libservicelog is not already installed on the system library path, the
test suite currently fails because the library cannot be found.  This also
means that the library being tested by the test suite is *not* the one in
the source tree, but the one installed on the system.

This is fixed by linking against the libtool .la instead of directly against
the .so, so that we get a wrapper script that sets the LD_LIBRARY_PATH.

Signed-off-by: Steve Langasek <steve.langasek@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Ankit Kumar <ankit@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: Vasant Hegde <hegdevasant@linux.vnet.ibm.com>

Validate text string before and after bind call

While binding string to query, if string is NULL then bind call gets ignored.
While fetching data from string, if data is NULL then current code makes query
as NULL and returns.

This patch validates text string before and after bind call. It assigns string
to "" incase data is NULL points to NULL pointer. After this we will be able
to display information even if some of string data is NULL.

It also does NULL checks for compulsory string.

libservicelog: Fixes issue related to pipe()

There are issues in run_notification_tool() function:

  - When pipe() is not called and fork() passes, which need some check

This patch fixes above issues and also adds dup2() failure case.
